= Description =
{{Blurimage|file=Midrooms.jpeg|caption=A section resembling Level 0.}}
Agglomeration, nicknamed as '''"The Midrooms"''', is a very unique level in the Backrooms. Unlike most levels, it does not have a fixed appearance, as it only imitates other levels. It presents itself as a mix of every level in the Backrooms, ranging from [[Level 0]] to [[Level 1000]] to even other anomalous levels like [[the Hub]].<br>

Due to this level's special property, one may stumble upon [[Level 0|mono yellow carpets]], yet around the corner there are [[Level 2|pipes lined up on the walls]]. The pattern of these areas is completely unpredictable, making exploring a very confusing experience.<br>

This level is affected by extreme [[Phenomenon 14|Shifting Geometry]], causing the environment to transform when unobserved. As a result, travelling long distances has rendered difficult, so groups should always stick together whenever they can to prevent getting lost.<br>

One may get confused once they enter the level randomly, as the destination may not be the one expected. To leave this level, the wanderer should noclip in an area that resembles the level they were previously in. Any attempt to noclip in unmatched areas always results in a failure.<br>

There is a low chance where the environment transforms inside a person, trapping them inside a wall or the floor, killing them instantly. This made surviving and documenting information from this level unexpectedly difficult.<br>

This level contains an abundant amount of [[Object 32|Corruptionite]] (Note: The fact that the Trailblazers didn't encounter any of them is incredible), they commonly appear in clumps of viscous liquid leaking out from the walls. They burn and melt everything they touch, sometimes starting fires.<br>

There are zero resources or other exits in this level, making entering it completely impractical and meaningless.<br>

{{Blurimage|file=Level 2 and Level 3.webp|caption=A mixture of Level 2 and Level 3.}}
'''Level Mixing''' is a special property in this level that allows two or more level-lookalikes to combine together, creating an environment that shares characteristics from those levels. It often form coherent structures, but sometimes they are completely unrecognizable due to the amount of levels mixed in.<br>

These locations are more unstable than standalone areas, increasing hidden danger. Wanderers who find themselves situated in them should be more careful about their surroundings.<br>
=<small> The Broken </small>=
Many have theorized the relation between this level and [[the Broken]] because of their similarities. They are both environmentally unstable, mixtures of other levels, and have constantly changing geometry.<br>

This theory is confirmed as it is found that wanderering too far in this level slowly transforms it into the Broken.<br>
